text: Johnson County is a county in the U.S. state of Wyoming. The population was 8,447 as of the 2020 census. The county seat is Buffalo. The only other incorporated town in the county is Kaycee. == Communities == === City === * Buffalo (county seat) === Town === * Kaycee === Unincorporated communities === * Hazelton * Linch * Saddlestring * Sussex ==References== == Other websites == * Johnson County official website Category:Wyoming counties Category:1881 establishments in the United States Category:1880s establishments in Wyoming Territory
